  "text": "The systolic blood pressure (SBP) of each rat (08:00 am-10:00 am) was monitored by tail-cuff plethysmography (BP-98A; Softron, Tokyo, Japan), which correlates well with telemetry measurement of SBP [CITATION_1] . Briefly, each rat was warmed to 38°C and SBP was assessed continuously 15 times, in which 3 continuous values of variation of less than 6 mmHg were averaged to define maternal SBP.",
